history.content: The department consent required flag -- which seems to forbid students to add themselves to the waitlist -- has been removed.  Apologies on behalf of campus for the confusion.  Students should now be able to add themselves to the waitlist.

I read on this page that the first step to getting enrolled in the class is to have all the team members get on the wait list. My issue is that even if I try to get on the wait list (by checking the add to wait list if class full box) I get the same error that I get if I try to enroll: 

Error: Department Consent Required. You must obtain permission to take this class. If you have a permission number, select Add Another Class, select the class link, enter the number and resubmit.

Has anyone successfully got on the waitlist and/or know how would I go about doing this?

By the way, I am a declared CS major still having the other problem enrolling in other upper div classes as well.
history.subject: How to get on wait list for 169
